TextBlock.TextLine: Adij 30 maij 1697
Londen charles tollengeere
in ontwort aenduwe van 27 passato & 14 deser hebbe ul gecrediteert mee
voor st £ 366:- betaelt aen d'ordre van m. thomas potter, gelieve p naesten
te noteeren ul provisie & oncosten en te ordonneeren dat ick het gene ul sal
te goet comen aen mijn Cosijn Elias betaelen om onse reeckenige te sluyten
ter wijlen dat ick het soo weet sal aensien, ten waere als ul noteert de wissel
merckelijck quam te daelen & eenich voordeel ordeelde ul te remitteeren om te
naer dincomen van pennigen pr. wissel te laeten afcomen in welcke gosalle
wensche wel te wete tot wat prijs ul mij sal dienen voor proisie & del
credre te staen van ul remises, op de vallende wissel van costij wil hier
niemant geven, daer en tusschen worden geen brieven onder de 35 &3 gelaete
het gene supponeere int cort sal veranderen om de reden door ul gementioneert
onder tusschen ul voordere opinie daerover somtijdt naer dat ul gelegen valt
sal mij aengenaem wesen
30 maij
Londres Jaque S cabrol
J'aj lhonneur de la vre de 25 passé p. la quelle ie vous vre civelite &
linclination que vous aves pour corresponder avec moij & que vous me
serviray avec un grande affection & pntualite ie vous suis ablige de
vous remarcie de vre bonte vous assurant que ie feray du mesme
si vous aves besoing mes services a ces quatiers pandant que ie me ne
prevaleres pas de cette bonne occasionches vous dierant la guerre a go
Amst geraert rover
maij
sijn keer, sedert mijnen lesten van 27 deser geen van ul de Amst beirtley
blijven manqueren: brieven van 14 van londen seggen als dat de excquert
briefsiens beginhen in groot nomber uijt te comen waervore om gelt
te krijgen 5 a 6 p. wart gegeven & dat de selve naer propositie van
den agio cours sullen in wissel, waer door de selve merckelijck soude
daelen te meer omdat daer aengenomen is 2 millionen ten dienst
van den Coninck in vlaenderen te fourniere a 32s waerop die voor
eerst echter maer op 36t is gevallen hier geen gevers en onder de
35 t verliet niemant sijn brieven het welck sich sal governeeren
naer advenant het costij sal gaen, dief versoecke den prijs van morgen
te vernemen & expeditie aen d'ingeslotene. blijve.
30 maij
London walter & William kent
mij last to you was 27: courant, the contents whereof, pray consider
principalley about the sp. clothes, because I observe, that I mush bee
better assorted of cosfie coullours, as well under 67 a ƒ 7„ 7:6 „ 8 N 1o10
a 12st, so as then expressed, the same in the draps butt the cooperrose
must bee most part under & att 7t that cullour doth not sell so well
in high priees. now have bfore mee irs of 11 et 14 court with accompt
of woi1 shipt aboard george watson with w.10 & as you mention dese
for rotterdam with tlhe transport ships, & chare well arrived except said
watson, who theij say il lest behinde as if hee would not have ventured
under that convoij: I hope this not worse & that hee bee well expectinge
an other convoij of loch I longe to heare, perhaps hee stayes for the lone
that is to bring over the ambassadour mijlord williamson, bij w opportint
you might send some more sp. clothes bayes & principalley flannels beside
there is shippinge & a s0 regiment. for flaendres weh s sippose is feroste
for w a very good convoij must bee given, so that I should thinke, that
a good opportunitie to ship some goods for ostend, where in as all the rest
oft my concernes please to actt as for yours self, the spa clothes that snow
ordered in severall letters will make up 6 a 3 baces, the flannels must bee
fhe most part of the lowest prices you can finde, for though 1 n pr. y more 276
will save 2 in goodness, yett I must have of that commod, of what I cangue
give cheap some of 18 a 19 di maij bee in reach bale butt non to exeed 192 lett
syot next note the price of colchester white bayes, and when you iudge time
they maj bee cheapest to order wintes provision of them, whilst pray loose
no oppottunitie te forward what of white is mentioned in the memorandam
I longe to see the first letters from london to knowe if ex. will continue
tallinge, af they tell mee, al if itt must, because 2 millions are under taken to
bee furnisied here at 32 t, yett our drawers woult not abate thier price
shulday, asled 355, butt no givers, so please to exspect till next week
when shall remitt you whilst I rest
rotterdam Jaquer Meyers
Adij 3 Junij 1681
bij den uwen van 31 passato, geerne gesien dat george whatson costij voor
de stadt was gearriveert en dat ul divoir soude doen, mijne 2 packen ten
eersten te doen lossen, het welck ul andermael recommandere, dat geene
tijdt versuymt worde tot d'expeditie der selve, omdat mij daer aen il
gelegen versoeckende advies van de versendinge om tijdelijcke ordre te stellen
tot de verclaringe aen de marie daer sijn noch goederen aen boort voor
vrinden van dese plaets en soude niet geerne sien sij de selve voor mij
ontfongen, soo haest het convoij naer hull toegestaen is sult mij vercblige
s 1 ren het selve te laeten weten en d'expeditie aen dingeslotene blijve
hull william sohrson

in answer to y of 5 past I do not know al yett ywu toth the comissions of
mo kent jth, there in, I can do you no service hee beinge to sheeliver mj
goods aboard: there is a convoij ready in tessel for hull & may bee witth
you by this time, they write from Amst said convoij to bee 8 men of
warr, so shipt for mee what m. potter shall send you for my accompt for
Amstm & whereas scippose, that you are acquainted with the corresporder
of m: kent, so hee can tell you in what ships hee shall or hath shipped, the
packes N. 10 & 11 that to you schip mij packes frommipotter in other
vessels, because I would not have above one bule att the utmots 2 in
one bottom. l'avrite this day to m. kent, that hee orderet his frind att hull
to give you notice of my packes, butt lett him no know, that you schip
wollen goods for mee, that its bee to ship anoy lead swheate, or rye, or the
like, beside please no to ship anney packes for mee, till convoij presentes
& advise what passes to take mj mesures accordingley about en surance,
scipposeinge the custome with you al in london in case of a lors, that the
ensuradout payes butt 85 p. (to weh is the needfull att present from
ill ds thomas potter
so
mij last to you was 30 past, sence non trom you, butt have receaved the clots
you bought for mee, w in qualitie & call: can pass, butt the dreslinge ought
to bee better & shorter trimmed inclosed a patt. of N.9 where by you will see that
itt is left to long in hef wool, & so they are in generall, wherein pleake to take
care you tye tthe clothes with silk ruboons insteed whereof praiy take green
thread riebons of the qualitie & broadness to the inclosed patt. these packes sent
are to small, because all the petie charges are the same, as mugh on a s mall
as on a bigger pack, therefore the bayes must bee in one pack & ne lest then go
karsyes in one pack, & as swritt to you 2o past make the packes of clothes no less
then 16 demyepieces, as now I say make them up to 20 ps each pack in call
& instructions send 25m april & 20 the past, butt you may not bee backward
because thereis a convoij departed from Amst for hull, & .k if can come safe
here againe before the lattes of july then shall in order an orther alsortement ter
winter, so pray take measures accordingley & to loose no time, sent forward to
hull, what shall bee ready though the packes of clothes should bee assorted
